title: Body On I-90 Identified
text:
October 2, 2015, 4:02 PM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
The teenager found dead on Interstate 90 has been identified as an O'Gorman High School student. 
Authorities believe 16-year-old Jay Lavender was hit by a semi a mile east of the Interstate 29 interchange, near the North Kiwanis Avenue bridge. 
Witnesses say a semi was parked a quarter mile west of where Lavender was found before it drove away. The truck was described as white with a large grill and a closed trailer. 
The Minnehaha County Sheriff's Office is searching for the driver as part of its investigation. 
If you have any information, call authorities at 605-367-4300. 
The O'Gorman community is mourning the loss of one of our students who died in a tragic accident last night. Earlier...
